        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 1:29PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 129 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 4 miles southwest of Gans to 10 miles south of
Albion. Movement was northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Alma...                           Octavia...
Shibley...                        Kibler...
Cameron...                        Pocola...
Spiro...                          Big Cedar...
Cowlington...                     Rye Hill...
Poteau...                         Moffett...
Shady Point...                    Panama...
Fort Smith...                     Howe...
Excelsior...                      Whitesboro...
Fort Smith Regional Airport...    Van Buren...

This includes the following highways,
Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 0 and 14.
Interstate 40 in Oklahoma between mile markers 320 and 328.
Interstate 540 between mile markers 1 and 14.
Interstate 49 between mile markers 22 and 26.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for northwestern
and west central Arkansas...and southeastern and east central
Oklahoma.</instruction>
